Therefore the root-cause is localized to the service-level component ts-food-map-service. The most likely failure reason from the available choices is high CPU usage (due to traffic overload), manifested as high service latency. No socket errors or explicit error logs were found to indicate networking or application exceptions, and memory and socket metrics did not show comparable anomalous deviations at the earliest fault time. 

